etymologies: 1920s; earliest use found in Mineralogical Abstracts. From German Quenselit from the name of Percy D. Quensel, Swedish mineralogist + -it

definitions: A rare mineral containing lead and manganese, occurring as opaque, black, tabular crystals.

notes.text: Quenselite is an oxide and hydroxide of lead and manganese, PbMnO₂(OH). Crystal system: monoclinic.
